<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="50" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 836/122.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Janes</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-01-17"><hi rend="italic">January 17,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Reports presidential decree signed 14th, which continues during 1909
                            tariff reduction of 20 per cent, favoring articles enjoying privilege
                            last year.</p>
                    </div>
